name: Spicy Air Fryer Wings
author: Paul Tannos
summary: Spicy dry rub wings made in the air fryer.
ingredients: 1 ½ pounds chicken wings and drummettes
1 teaspoon cayenne pepper, or more to taste
directions: Place in a large bowl, drizzle with oil, and toss to coat
Combine paprika, chili powder, cumin, onion powder, garlic powder, black pepper, salt, and cayenne in a small bowl
Sprinkle over chicken and toss until evenly covered
Preheat an air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions
Arrange chicken in the basket of the preheated air fryer in a single layer, not touching
Cook until no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 12 minutes, turning halfway through
An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C)
For crispier wings, increase temperature to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) and cook for 2 to 3 minutes more
Let rest for a few minutes before serving
